fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.themes

Interface ITemplateFile

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Comparable<ITemplateFile>, IAttachable

    public interface ITemplateFile
extends IAttachable, Comparable<ITemplateFile>
    Represents a template for dynamically-generated content.

    Implementations will override Object.hashCode() and Object.equals(Object) for effective usage as collection keys.

    Thread safety: implementations are required to be safe for concurrent access.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies

      • merge

        void merge(ITemplateData data,
           Writer out)
    throws IOException
        Merges data with the template to produce a displayable result, in the supplied output writer, for text format templates. The writer encoding should be UTF-8. If this template can only produce binary format results, an exception will be thrown.
        Parameters:
        data - non-null dataset to merge with the template.
        out - target for output. The target writer is not closed by this method, although it should be flushed when this method returns.
        Throws:
        IOException - if merging or output fails, or if the template can only produce binary format results.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        createDataContext(), isBinaryOnly()

      • merge

        void merge(ITemplateData data,
           OutputStream out)
    throws IOException
        Merges data with the template to produce a displayable result, in the supplied output stream, for text or binary format templates. If this is a text format template, the text output should by default be assumed to be encoded as UTF-8.
        Parameters:
        data - non-null dataset to merge with the template.
        out - target for output. The target stream is not closed by this method, although it should be flushed when this method returns.
        Throws:
        IOException - if merging or output fails.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        createDataContext(), isBinaryOnly()

      • isBinaryOnly

        boolean isBinaryOnly()
        Indicates if this template can only produce results using a binary output stream.
        Returns:
        true if merging with a Writer is not supported, otherwise false.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        merge(ITemplateData, java.io.Writer), merge(ITemplateData, java.io.OutputStream)
